HEADWORD: Wonderment
<hw>Won"der*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Surprise;
astonishment; a wonderful appearance; a wonder.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the common sights they view,⟦br⟧
Their <qex>wonderment</qex> engage.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wonderous</ent>⟦br⟧
